<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41041c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41041c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41041c"> 41(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> access to idiot / = rape</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If a woman of unsound mind is in such a <mark>state of idiocy</mark> as to be incapable of expressing either consent or dissent, connections with her <mark>amounts to rape</mark>; but otherwise the consent of such a woman, induced by mere animal instinct, is sufficient to prevent the act from constituting a rape. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 82</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
